{
    "word": "Sardonic",
    "definitions": [
        "Of, pertaining to, or resembling, a kind of linen made at Colchis."
    ],
    "examples": [
        "Where strained, sardonic smiles are glozing still, And grief is forced to laugh against her will.",
        "The scornful, ferocious, sardonic grin of a bloody ruffian."
    ],
    "etymology": "[F. sardonique, L. sardonius, Gr. Sardinia, Gr. Forced; unnatural; insincere; hence, derisive, mocking, malignant, or bitterly sarcastic; -- applied only to a laugh, smile, or some facial semblance of gayety. [1913 Webster]"
}